{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockref\/readerlock()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerLock"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_rw_lock_reader_lock()"},{"type":"text","text":" while the current thread already"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"owns a write lock leads to undefined behaviour. Read locks however"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be taken recursively, in which case you need to make sure to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_rw_lock_reader_unlock()"},{"type":"text","text":" the same amount of times."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is implementation-defined how many read locks are allowed to be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"held on the same lock simultaneously. If the limit is hit,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or if a deadlock is detected, a critical warning will be emitted.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockRef\/RWLockProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerLock"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"readerLock()","extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib14RWLockProtocolPAAE10readerLockyyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib9RWLockRefV","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockRef\/readerLock()"},"abstract":[{"text":"Obtain a read lock on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"text":". If another thread currently holds","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the write lock on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":", the current thread will block until the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"write lock was (held and) released. If another thread does not hold"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the write lock, but is waiting for it, it is implementation defined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the reader or writer will block. Read locks can be taken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recursively.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"title":"Mutex","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockRef/readerLock()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/r